ttp://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The relay team - Caeleb Dressel, Jack Alexy, Chris Guiliano, and Hunter Armstrong - pulled ahead of Australia by 1.07 seconds.\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 220, \"end\": 224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"score\": 0.9993161391773091, \"rank\": 0.0006842866785145463, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\"}, {\"begin\": 287, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9989434399320332, \"rank\": 0.0010429355295026943, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy earned the bronze medal.\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9751220476799222, \"rank\": 0.020633155808577004, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA has dominated the event, having won 10 of the last 13 Olympics, with Dressel earning his eighth Olympic gold in Paris on Saturday.\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.999999507965079, \"rank\": 4.909926242665737e-07, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 466, \"end\": 471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999991240662637, \"rank\": 8.759345625011484e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prior to the men's gold win, the U.S. women's 4\\u00d7100-meter freestyle relay team - comprising Kate Douglass, Gretchen Walsh, Torri Huske, and Simone Manuel - won silver during their event and set a new American record in the event with a time of 3:30.20.\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 578, \"end\": 591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torri Huske\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\"}, {\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999961331645593, \"rank\": 3.858705109173518e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia took the gold and set a new Olympic record with 3:28.92, and China earned bronze.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 739, \"end\": 748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9989434399320332, \"rank\": 0.0010429355295026943, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 810, \"end\": 815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.925454619305044, \"rank\": 0.08048230769924089, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. earned its first medal in Paris with Sarah Bacon and Kassidy Cook taking home silver in the 3-meter synchronized springboard competition.Trending StoriesJohn Lithgow Knows J.K. Rowling's Anti-Trans Views Will Now Forever Come Up in 'Every Interview'Kevin Spacey's 'Mental Illness' Should Trigger $29.5 Million Payout, 'House of Cards' Trial Jurors HearBTS Nails Its Comeback With 'Arirang'Top Disaster Response Official Claims He Teleported to a Waffle House  Team USA's Katie Ledecky also medaled in the women's freestyle final, taking home the bronze.\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 867, \"end\": 872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999991240662637, \"rank\": 8.759345625011484e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\", \"score\": 0.9999783626862015, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sarah Bacon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\"}, {\"begin\": 894, \"end\": 906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kassidy_Cook\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kassidy Cook\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"ht